	</doc><doc for="CodeExpressionStatement">
		<summary>
			<para> Represents a statement that consists of a single expression.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para><see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeExpressionStatement"/> can represent a
   statement that consists of a single expression.</para>
			<para>A <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeExpressionStatement"/> contains a <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeExpression"/>, and
it can be added to a <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeStatementCollection"/>, allowing some expressions to stand alone. For
example, a <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeMethodInvokeExpression"/> contained by a
<see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeExpressionStatement"/> can represent a method call without a 
return value. </para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<codelink SampleID="CodeDomSampleBatch" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
